# Mandatory project standards

## Essential reading

You **must** read **`docs/coding-standards.md`** before writing or changing Vala code. This is not optional — do not guess conventions and do not implement until you have read it.

Also read when the task requires it:

- **`docs/build-rules.md`** — build or Meson changes
- **`docs/code-documentation.md`** — docblocks and API comments
- **`docs/guide-to-writing-plans.md`** — work from `docs/plans/*`
- **`docs/bug-fix-process.md`** — bug fixes

## Rules (every Vala change)

- **No new methods** — no helpers unless the user or plan asks; inline in the method you touch
- **Type identifiers** — no `Type?` except external boundaries; `GLib.` prefix; no `using`
- **Temporary variables** — no single-use locals; no property aliases; inline unless 4+ deep
- **Build** — `ninja -C build` only; never `valac`

Canonical detail: **`docs/coding-standards.md`**. Plans: **`docs/guide-to-writing-plans.md`** — Checklist for plans.
